</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation id="133225E55748FFACFC375879FB9D2302" box="[936,1066,561,587]" captionStart="FIGURES 43–48" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1931,1955]" captionTargetBox="[165,1411,691,1889]" captionTargetId="figure-217@14.[151,1435,669,1907]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 43–48. Female of Atelurius segmentatus. Habitus (MCN 36915): 43 dorsal view, white arrow: chevrons coloration pattern; 44 ventral view, white arrow: ventrally chitinized plate; 45 lateral view; 46 face, frontal view. Scale bars: 1 mm. Epigyne female 47 ventral; 48 dorsal. Scale bars: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417694" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417694/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="446">Figs 47–48</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="133225E55748FFACFBAA5879FBE32305" box="[1077,1108,561,588]" captionStart="FIGURE 65–70" captionStartId="20.[151,250,1877,1901]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,181,1853]" captionTargetId="figure-22@20.[151,1435,181,1853]" captionTargetPageId="20" captionText="FIGURE 65–70. Scanning electronic microscopy (SEM). Male of Si. gladifer (MCTP 31078): 65 carapace surface, 66 claw surface. Female of A. segmentatus (MCN 401182): 67 carapace surface, 68 epigyne ventral view. Subadult Guriurius minuano sp. nov. (MCN 32225): 69 carapace surface, 70 male epiandric spigots." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417705" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417705/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="446">68</figureCitation>
), 
<typeStatus id="54B287C25748FFACFBF7587AFB2F2305" box="[1128,1176,562,588]" pageId="15" pageNumber="446">type</typeStatus>
species of the genus, it is possible to propose the transfer of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35748FFACFDA9581EFB9B2326" authority="Perger &amp; Rubio, 2018" authorityName="Perger &amp; Rubio" authorityYear="2018" box="[566,1068,597,624]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Scoturius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dipterioides">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725748FFACFDA9581EFC9A2326" box="[566,813,597,624]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="446">Scoturius dipterioides</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9844915748FFACFCAA581EFB9B2326" author="Perger, R. &amp; Rubio, G. D." box="[821,1068,597,624]" pageId="15" pageNumber="446" pagination="0190582" refId="ref17655" refString="Perger, R. &amp; Rubio, G. D. (2018) A wolf in sheep's clothing: The description of a fly resembling jumping spider of the genus Scoturius Simon, 1901 (Araneae: Salticidae: Huriini). PLoS One, 13 (1), e 0190582. https: // doi. org / 10.1371 / journal. pone. 0190582" type="journal article" year="2018">Perger &amp; Rubio, 2018</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0942E35748FFACFBCE581DFAE72326" authority="Simon, 1901" authorityName="Simon" authorityYear="1901" box="[1105,1360,597,623]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Atelurius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="446" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B97DE5725748FFACFBCE581DFB0F2326" box="[1105,1208,597,623]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="446">Atelurius</emphasis>
Simon, 1901
</taxonomicName>
, based on the morphology of the copulatory ducts. We suggest that the membranous portion (CD*) of copulatory ducts were not illustrated by the authors (compare with 
<figureCitation id="133225E55748FFACFD5958D5FCAE23FE" box="[710,793,669,695]" captionStart="FIGURES 43–48" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1931,1955]" captionTargetBox="[165,1411,691,1889]" captionTargetId="figure-217@14.[151,1435,669,1907]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 43–48. Female of Atelurius segmentatus. Habitus (MCN 36915): 43 dorsal view, white arrow: chevrons coloration pattern; 44 ventral view, white arrow: ventrally chitinized plate; 45 lateral view; 46 face, frontal view. Scale bars: 1 mm. Epigyne female 47 ventral; 48 dorsal. Scale bars: 0.10 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6417694" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6417694/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="446">Fig. 48</figureCitation>
: * asterisks to the membranous copulatory ducts).
</paragraph>
